<statement>
<p>
A population of bacteria is growing according to the equation <m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1950}{e}^{{{0.08}{t}}}</m>.  Estimate when the population will exceed 3028.</p>
<p>
<em>t</em>= <fillin characters="20"/> Â  </p>
<p>
Give your answer accurate to one decimal place.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.5009120374943</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1950}{e}^{{{0.08}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{3028}={1950}{e}^{{{0.08}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{3028}}{{1950}}={e}^{{{0.08}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{\ln{{\left(\frac{{3028}}{{1950}}\right)}}}={0.08}{t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{\ln{{\left(\frac{{3028}}{{1950}}\right)}}}}{{0.08}}={t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{t}={5.5009120374943}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>